File: PSL Chairperson Irvin Khoza. JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League season is set to resume on 8 August. The season will restart with the Nedbank Cup semi-finals. All PSL teams will be based in Gauteng. READ: Absa, PSL announce end to Absa Premiership sponsorshi PSL Chairman Irvin Khoza announced the league's resumption during a media briefing on Monday. Kaizer Chiefs are at the top of the PSL table. Matches were halted in March by the coronavirus pandemic.